It's over there.

65
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,520
"Miyagawa's expedition
in Amami Islands"

66
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:53,920
This place is incredible!

67
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,160
Wow, look at that.

68
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,480
It's pretty.

69
00:02:57,560 --> 00:02:59,240
What a great view.

70
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,560
"Miyazon's autumn leaves tour"

71
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:01,920
It's incredible.

72
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:04,520
A great adventure is about to start.

73
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:08,040
Miyagawa Expedition

74
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:11,280
in Amami Islands,
Kagoshima Prefecture.

75
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,440
Miyagawa Expedition.

76
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:15,200
When you watch it,
you can tell it's the real deal.

77
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:19,680
It's our 14th expedition, and we're
visiting Amami Islands, Kagoshima!

78
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:25,240
First, they explore Amami Oshima,
the biggest island of Amami Islands.

79
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:28,280
Here are the four members
of the expedition.

80
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:30,600
Director Kitami,
also known as Chappu.

81
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:31,840
Assistant producer Yoshizawa,

82
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:33,200
and Assistant Director Iwashita.

83
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,240
Also...

84
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:35,440
Hirata.

85
00:03:35,520 --> 00:03:38,160
Also known as Okasan.

86
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:39,360
People often call me so.

87
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:41,520
Yeah, I know that.

88
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:43,040
What are you wearing?

89
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:45,440
You intentionally
try to look like a mother.

90
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,200
But you're well prepared.

91
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,720
I like that about you!

92
00:03:50,280 --> 00:03:52,440
You're trying to make people laugh.

93
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,920
That helps me a lot.

94
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,600
- It helps.
- Nice.

95
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:57,400
The first mission is

96
00:03:57,480 --> 00:04:01,720
to capture the legendary and rare
Amami rabbit on camera.

97
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:05,720
Nature guide Masahiro Nishi
will assist in the expedition.

98
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:08,640
As an animal, Amami rabbit made
the first natural monument in Japan.

99
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:13,840
They're a special natural monument,
which is the highest rank.

100
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:17,760
The same species existed
in Mainland China before.

101
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:20,440
But when Amami Islands got separated
from Mainland China,

102
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:23,240
that species went extinct
in Mainland China.

103
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:28,280
Now, they only exist in Amami Oshima
and Tokunoshima.

104
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:29,600
I'm curious.

105
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:32,880
I see something written
on your left hand. What is it?

106
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:37,760
I had to tell the district leader
that we'd be filming here today.

107
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,840
I wrote down, "district leader."

108
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,880
I thought I'd forget it otherwise.

109
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,480
Like an elementary school kid.

110
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:44,960
That's all.

111
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,720
About two million years ago,
due to tectonic shifting,

112
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,800
the islands got separated
from Mainland China.

113
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:53,000
Ever since then, the islands
kept their own ecosystem.

114
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:57,120
It's a place filled with rare
animals, including Amami rabbits.

115
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,480
But most of the animals
are nocturnal.

116
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,240
So during the day...

117
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:03,840
If you find something that looks
like food, please let me know.

118
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:08,560
they'll look for food
in Amami's forest and sea.

119
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,800
Can we eat this?

120
00:05:10,880 --> 00:05:11,720
Leader!

121
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,280
You scared me!

122
00:05:13,360 --> 00:05:14,600
What is it?

123
00:05:14,680 --> 00:05:15,560
Look at this.

124
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:17,360
Behind the leaves.

125
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,320
What are they?

126
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,280
What are they? They look creepy!

127
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,720
They're stink bugs.

128
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,520
"Stink bugs gathered in one place"

129
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,720
That looks creepy!

130
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:30,880
They basically don't move at all
when it's hot during summer.

131
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:33,640
- They gather in one place and rest.
- No way.

132
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:36,120
Since you have that camera...

133
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,160
I'll shoot them up close.

134
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:41,520
Could you also do the narration?

135
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:46,040
Since the last expedition,
the young director Kitami started

136
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:48,520
training himself
to do impromptu narration.

137
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:51,520
It's been one month now.
How much did he improve?

138
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,400
- Let's see.
- I have an idea.

139
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,680
Okay, go ahead.

140
00:05:54,760 --> 00:06:00,800
A large amount of stink bugs gather
in a cool place during summer.

141
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:04,000
The way they stick
to the backs of the leaves

142
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:07,440
resembles ripe grapes.

143
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,520
You can tell yourself.

144
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:14,000
Here, Leader finds food.

145
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:16,200
Wow, what is this?

146
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,160
They're snake gourds.

147
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,400
Snake gourds.

148
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,920
It's a plant in the gourd family.

149
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,480
But they bear fruit four metres
above the ground.

150
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,760
It's not easy to reach them.

151
00:06:27,840 --> 00:06:29,800
- I came up with a strategy.
- Okay.

152
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:35,280
Kitami and Leader,
please hold each other's shoulders.

153
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,320
I'll go on top of you guys,

154
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,800
and drop the gourds with a branch.

155
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:39,840
That's my strategy.

156
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,000
I'll go up.

157
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,960
That's how it should be.

158
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,440
How much do you weigh?

159
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,200
Sixty-seven kilograms.

160
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:49,320
Eighty kilograms.

161
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:51,600
Seventy-eight kilograms.

162
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,560
So it's you.

163
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,280
Let's get it started!

164
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:58,680
- Slowly.
- Here it goes.

165
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,280
Ouch, don't pull my hair.

166
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,920
- Don't pull my hair.
- I'm falling!

167
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,720
I'm falling!

168
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,320
Watch out!

169
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:13,240
Leader was hit strongly on his nose.

170
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,840
That hurt.

171
00:07:14,920 --> 00:07:16,960
You went down this way.

172
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,560
This part dropped.

173
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,280
This strategy won't work.

174
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:24,400
Next, they decided to make a loop
with their rope,

175
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,720
and try to hook the fruit with it.

176
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,480
- I'm scared.
- It's fine.

177
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,480
Okasan will give it a try.

178
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:32,600
Below her is Iwashita.

179
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,680
Here we go.

180
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,240
"Iwashita's quiet battle begins now"

181
00:07:35,320 --> 00:07:38,400
Iwashita's quiet battle begins now.

182
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:41,280
Step forward a bit, Iwashita.

183
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,480
Forward.

184
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,960
It's an important job.

185
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,440
You can do it!

186
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:48,600
You can do it!

187
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,080
Almost there. Once again.

188
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:52,160
Keep going, Iwashita.

189
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,960
Okay, nice. You go it.

190
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:57,080
- Wait, wait.
- Hold it, hold it.

191
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,840
Now, all they need to do
is to pull the rope.

192
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,080
Okay, here we go.

193
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:04,400
We've got it! We got two of them!

194
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:07,360
After going through trouble,
they've got two snake gourds!

195
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,800
However...

196
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:14,120
What is this?

197
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,920
It stinks.

198
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,840
They were too ripe to be eaten.

199
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:23,040
Next, they find Amami
short-horned grasshoppers,

200
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:25,120
which is in the same family
as rice grasshopper.

201
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,280
Can you capture it?
This is our only chance.

202
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,920
So quick.

203
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,480
The grasshoppers that they captured

204
00:08:32,560 --> 00:08:35,640
will be boiled and seasoned
with Japanese silver leaf,

205
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:38,200
which is an Asteraceae plant
growing on the island.

206
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:40,320
We're at the sea!

207
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,400
Next, they'll try to find seafood.

208
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:46,200
Flip over large rocks like that.

209
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,120
If you dig ground underneath it,

210
00:08:48,200 --> 00:08:52,080
you might be able to find
large mud crabs.

211
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:55,880
They're large crabs that are
more than 20 centimetres long.

212
00:08:55,960 --> 00:08:58,680
Give me a shovel.

213
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,560
Shovel.

214
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,720
Oh, yeah, that's right.

215
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:07,240
"The Ant and the Grasshopper.

216
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:12,400
The sun is burning the fields
and forests.

217
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,480
It's hot..."

218
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:17,000
It was quick today.

219
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:18,120
The baby's asleep.

220
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,200
Are you asleep?

221
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,040
Good night. You idiot!

222
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,720
This is "Aesop's Fable."

223
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,960
I meant "shovel".

224
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:30,080
Why did you hand me "Aesop's Fable"?

225
00:09:32,080 --> 00:09:35,280
Oh, yeah, that's right.

226
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:39,440
I like thin ones rather than
thick ones. This one is thick.

227
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:41,400
Let's eat.

228
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:46,640
I love sukonbu. You idiot!

229
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:49,440
This is sukonbu.

230
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:51,600
I panicked a bit
when you handed this to me.

231
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:54,920
I told you to give me a shovel,
and you gave me this.

232
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:56,440
I panicked quite a bit.

233
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,280
I was really anxious. You idiot.

234
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,760
This isn't the right one.
I need a shovel.

235
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,120
Do you know what this is?

236
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,200
Does he know what it is?

237
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,840
That's right, this is it.

238
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,280
This is it.

239
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,240
This...

240
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,520
Yeah, I know what this is.

241
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,120
Woohoo...

242
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,520
Woohoo...

243
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:24,440
What?

244
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:26,320
Woohoo...

245
00:10:27,560 --> 00:10:30,000
What is this?

246
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:33,840
- Sawadee kap.
- Sawadee kap!

247
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:36,280
Sawadee kap!

248
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,640
How would he know?

249
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,800
How would I know that?

250
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:42,120
Let's get back to mud crabs.

251
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:44,200
Oh, look!

252
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,480
That's not it.

253
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,520
That's not it!

254
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,360
I caught two animals.
Are they edible?

255
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,720
No, they aren't.

256
00:10:51,800 --> 00:10:54,960
Unfortunately,
they couldn't find mud crabs.

257
00:10:55,040 --> 00:10:56,600
But in the river...

258
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:58,200
I've got it.

259
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,640
He's good.

260
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:02,880
He found freshwater prawn, which is
a speciality of Amami Oshima.

261
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,200
I'm so happy.

262
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:07,480
With everyone joining forces,
they caught this many prawns.

263
00:11:07,560 --> 00:11:09,640
They also found something perfect
for dessert.

264
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,880
- Bananas.
