00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:53,960
It's a tough route that has not
been maintained at all.

548
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:57,360
They move forward carefully.

549
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,000
- It's a coral fossil.
- Here it is.

550
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,280
This is it.

551
00:23:02,320 --> 00:23:07,560
This island was underwater before,
and corals grew there.

552
00:23:07,640 --> 00:23:11,640
Okinoerabujima is an island formed
by the uplift of a coral reef.

553
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:13,440
Therefore, the ground is fragile,

554
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:17,600
and numerous caves have been formed
by groundwater erosion.

555
00:23:17,680 --> 00:23:20,280
This part looks crazy.

556
00:23:20,360 --> 00:23:22,760
They pass an area
with a low ceiling again.

557
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:25,920
They crawl in water.

558
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,640
We should take a break.

559
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,200
Let's cool down.

560
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,160
Wait.

561
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:33,480
Chappu, Okasan,
you look like you're at the beach.

562
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:37,600
You look like a married couple
watching kids playing in water.

563
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:40,840
Here comes the hardest part
of the cave.

564
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:44,200
This tiny hole is the only way
to get past this area.

565
00:23:45,200 --> 00:23:46,800
This continues?

566
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,920
Yes, it continues to the back.

567
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,920
It's the hardest part.

568
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,000
This is crazy.

569
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:54,880
I barely fit in this.

570
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:58,240
It's only 20 centimetres from
the ceiling to the water surface.

571
00:23:58,320 --> 00:24:00,800
This place is insane!

572
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:03,320
They move forward slowly
while facing up.

573
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,400
Wow.

574
00:24:04,920 --> 00:24:08,640
It's dangerous when people panic,
so they all try to keep calm.

575
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:13,480
All of the members successfully pass
the hardest part of the cave.

576
00:24:13,560 --> 00:24:15,840
Now, they're halfway there.

577
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:18,880
From here on, the cave starts
to look completely different.

578
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,640
What is this?

579
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:24,640
It's a beautiful world
of stalactites.

580
00:24:24,720 --> 00:24:26,640
They're spirals.

581
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:27,640
Spirals.

582
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:32,040
They're spiralling
stalactite icicles called spirals.

583
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:34,040
Water drips quicker than the others.

584
00:24:34,120 --> 00:24:34,960
I see.

585
00:24:35,040 --> 00:24:37,560
- The shapes change based on that.
- Interesting.

586
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:39,480
This looks pretty.

587
00:24:39,560 --> 00:24:45,160
Calcium carbonate crystals
in stalactites sparkle.

588
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:48,720
It's rare to see particles this big.

589
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,160
They sparkle a lot.

590
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,480
You're right.

591
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:55,200
It's been three hours
since they entered the cave.

592
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:57,920
Once they go down
this vertical waterfall,

593
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,600
the goal will be near.

594
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,960
We're almost there!

595
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,840
- Okay.
