00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,680
What is that?

798
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,400
Hey, please don't push!

799
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:43,480
Wow, look at this!

800
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:47,680
It looks incredible
on the ground, too!

801
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:51,800
He is visiting Hitachi Seaside Park.

802
00:33:51,880 --> 00:33:56,400
There are fluffy ball-like plants
everywhere he sees.

803
00:33:57,400 --> 00:34:01,000
They are also autumn leaves that
can only be seen during this season.

804
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:03,800
These are kokia plants!

805
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:06,760
They're usually green
and look like round green algae.

806
00:34:06,840 --> 00:34:08,320
But during this season,

807
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:11,480
they change colours
and have a vivid red colour.

808
00:34:12,160 --> 00:34:15,320
Here, Miyazon has a quiz
about kokia.

809
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:18,560
Once withered,
this plant turns into something.

810
00:34:18,640 --> 00:34:20,040
What do you think it is?

811
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:22,160
- What is it?
- Mr Uchimura,

812
00:34:22,240 --> 00:34:24,800
answer me within one second.

813
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:27,880
One second has already passed,
but you're fine.

814
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:30,280
Really? It's okay?

815
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:33,160
I'm sorry. Wrong!

816
00:34:33,240 --> 00:34:35,680
Here's the answer.

817
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:37,040
I'm sorry.

818
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:38,800
- Here it is.
- What's going on?

819
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,040
Do you know what it is?

820
00:34:41,120 --> 00:34:42,000
A broom.

821
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,880
Here it is.

822
00:34:43,960 --> 00:34:47,120
It turns into a broom!

823
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:49,520
They're also known as broom plant.

824
00:34:49,600 --> 00:34:52,440
In olden times,
they used this plant to make brooms.

825
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:55,920
Belvedere fruit,
which is also known as field caviar,

826
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,600
is actually processed kokia seeds.

827
00:34:58,680 --> 00:35:00,640
I'll call this land coral leaf.

828
00:35:00,720 --> 00:35:01,560
That sounds good.

829
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:06,240
Miyazon wants to find
a great metaphor for kokia.

830
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:09,280
But "land coral leaf" is...

831
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:11,400
Someone has already said it.

832
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:13,720
Okay, let's come up
with something else.

833
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:15,560
This one is very unique.

834
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:16,880
Land...

835
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:18,640
round red algae.

836
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:19,800
How about that?

837
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,920
Land round green algae.

838
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,200
Round green algae...

839
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,240
- A lot has said that?
- Everyone.

840
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:26,920
Everyone calls it that.

841
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,800
Can I have one last thing?

842
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:31,080
Land soccer ball.

843
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:33,720
Land soccer ball
is just a soccer ball.

844
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,000
That's right.

845
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:38,720
Miyazon finds that someone else has
a great talent in using metaphors.

846
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:40,680
What kind of metaphor would you use?

847
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:44,880
For example, oysters are often
called "milk of the sea".

848
00:35:44,960 --> 00:35:47,160
A festive theatre of brooms.

849
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:50,320
He did better than me.

850
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,920
The goal in Aomori
is 550 kilometres away.

851
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:57,560
But here, he receives
unfortunate news.

852
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:58,520
We'll take a car from here.

853
00:35:58,600 --> 00:35:59,880
What?

854
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:01,120
Not a helicopter?

855
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,560
It's because of our budget.

856
00:36:02,640 --> 00:36:04,000
I see.

857
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,520
I'm staying positive.

858
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:06,960
If I said, "What? Why?

859
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,760
Why can't I take a helicopter?"

860
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:12,160
Then I'd sound like
a Hollywood star.

861
00:36:12,240 --> 00:36:15,000
So from here on,
they head north by car.

862
00:36:15,080 --> 00:36:19,320
They head to Narukokyo, a famous
autumn leaves spot in Tohoku.

863
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:24,440
Now, take a look at their
spontaneous trip to Narukokyo.

864
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:28,200
First is a great gyoza shop
in Utsunomiya, Tochigi Prefecture.

865
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:32,240
They have various kinds of gyoza,
and they're incredibly tasty.

866
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,520
But that wasn't it.

867
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:36,960
The shop owner was a folk singer,
and he started singing.

868
00:36:37,040 --> 00:36:40,320
That's the last one, so please eat
while listening to my song.

869
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:44,600
It's the very last

870
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:50,880
gyoza

871
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,960
It makes it hard to eat.

872
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:57,240
A lodge in Tochigi Prefecture
that takes forever to check in.

873
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,720
What?

874
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:00,880
Are we in Egypt?

875
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,240
Is this a pyramid?

876
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:06,680
This place is called
Pyramid Genki Onsen.

877
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:07,760
Welcome.

878
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:08,920
Thank you.

879
00:37:09,560 --> 00:37:10,880
- Nice to meet you.
- I like stuff like this.

880
00:37:10,960 --> 00:37:13,280
I'd like to stay
at this inn tonight.

881
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:16,280
Sure, no problem.

882
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:18,720
I hear "Fur Elise" playing.

883
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:20,880
Why did you build a pyramid?

884
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,720
It's because of the energy
of the universe.

885
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:25,200
- Okay.
- Well,

886
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:27,280
- it's a long time ago, but
- Okay.

887
00:37:27,360 --> 00:37:29,720
we had this thing
called Pyramid Power.

888
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:32,880
We gathered the energy here,

889
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:34,800
and concentrated it to one point.

890
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:37,200
We then put it in our bath.

891
00:37:37,280 --> 00:37:39,520
That's what we did.

892
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:43,480
Sorry, I couldn't hear anything
because of "Fur Elise".

893
00:37:43,560 --> 00:37:44,800
Thank you.

894
00:37:44,880 --> 00:37:46,280
I'll go in.

895
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:51,840
When he thought
he could finally check in...

896
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,960
That light there and this...

897
00:37:54,040 --> 00:37:56,880
He starts to talk
about the facility.

898
00:37:56,960 --> 00:38:01,640
I couldn't say no to him
because I knew he meant well.

899
00:38:01,720 --> 00:38:02,880
It lasted for about 30 minutes.

900
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:05,080
He told me about different things.

901
00:38:05,160 --> 00:38:08,920
If you lay down here,
you'll be asleep within 10 minutes.

902
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:09,920
How is it?

903
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,360
You'll get sleepy.

904
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:13,200
No matter what you're thinking,

905
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:16,320
it's okay,
because you'll get sleepy.

906
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:18,920
Can I check in now?

907
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,600
Sure.

908
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:23,480
Charred roasted pork
in Fukushima Prefecture.

909
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:25,000
It looks pretty!

910
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,240
Shirakawa Ramen

911
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:29,720
is a local speciality
of Shirakawa City, Fukushima.

912
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,200
- This looks great.
- It was great.

913
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:34,120
How nice.

914
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:35,560
It's incredible.

915
00:38:35,640 --> 00:38:37,800
The noodles are great.

916
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:40,080
Their roasted pork is also good.

917
00:38:40,160 --> 00:38:42,920
It's a bit charred...

918
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:46,080
How should I put it?
It has a good aroma.

919
00:38:46,160 --> 00:38:48,080
No, it's just burnt.

920
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:49,120
Really?

921
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:52,440
Cameraman Yamamoto's routine.

922
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:54,800
Here's Yamamoto.

923
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,280
- Is he studying something?
- He's taking medicine.

924
00:38:58,360 --> 00:39:00,240
What kind of medicine do you take?

925
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:01,560
For my blood pressure,

926
00:39:01,640 --> 00:39:03,760
- cholesterol,
- I'm worried about him.

927
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:06,400
- blood pressure,
- You're kidding.

928
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:08,280
- uric acid level,
- Don't go on a trip then.

929
00:39:08,360 --> 00:39:11,040
- allergy.
- It's hard to live.

930
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:15,040
Tsuruga Castle in Fukushima that
didn't have autumn leaves at all.

931
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:19,840
Is this it?
Illuminated autumn leaves.

932
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:23,800
This?

933
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,760
How did this happen?

934
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:28,680
He is the reason.

935
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:30,640
I'm Hoshi from the tourism division
of the city.

936
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:31,920
Mr Yuto Hoshi.

937
00:39:32,000 --> 00:39:35,040
Leaves are just starting
to change colours.

938
00:39:35,120 --> 00:39:37,240
You came here a bit too early.

939
00:39:37,320 --> 00:39:40,800
We were talking about
painting the leaves.

940
00:39:41,240 --> 00:39:43,480
Why didn't you tell me?

941
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:46,800
Because you wouldn't have come
if we told you.

942
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:52,320
Kaleidoscope Museum in Miyagi
that they visited unannounced.

943
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:53,840
Did you see that?

944
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:56,440
It says kaleidoscope. It's a museum.

945
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:58,800
I want to go
because I like sparkly things.

946
00:39:59,320 --> 00:40:00,440
He calls them right away.

947
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:01,720
I bought that at a roadside station.

948
00:40:01,800 --> 00:40:04,800
Thank you for calling,
this is Kaleidoscope Museum.

949
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:10,000
Hi there, my name is Miyazono.

950
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:14,200
I'm filming a show called
"The Quest".

951
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:17,400
- Okay.
- We're on a filming trip right now.

952
00:40:17,480 --> 00:40:18,480
Okay.

953
00:40:18,560 --> 00:40:21,480
We'd love to stop by at your museum.

954
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,640
When do you plan to visit?

955
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:26,800
Actually, we're already in front
of the museum entrance.

956
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:28,880
What?

957
00:40:28,960 --> 00:40:31,440
The most popular part of the museum
is a kaleidoscope

958
00:40:31,520 --> 00:40:33,960
into which you stick your head in,
perfect for Instagram.

959
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:36,600
It's pretty.

960
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:40,840
It feels like I'm inside
of a piece of jewel.

961
00:40:40,920 --> 00:40:43,640
- This looks nice.
- It reminds me of my childhood.

962
00:40:43,720 --> 00:40:45,560
My family was so poor

963
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:48,440
and we didn't have toys.

964
00:40:48,520 --> 00:40:52,280
So we'd get cardboard boxes
from a vegetable shop nearby.

965
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:55,040
I'd stick my head
in a cardboard box like this.

966
00:40:55,120 --> 00:40:58,520
It was a way for me
to be in my own world.

967
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:00,880
This reminds me of those times.

968
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:02,960
After three whole days,

969
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:07,120
Miyazon arrives
at Narukokyo, Miyagi Prefecture.

970
00:41:07,200 --> 00:41:09,280
- Wow!
- Everything is so short.

971
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:12,440
What a great view.

972
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,480
Incredible!

973
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:16,720
Natukokyo, Miyagi Prefecture.

974
00:41:16,800 --> 00:41:22,560
Sheer cliffs up to 100 metres deep
are covered in autumn leaves.

975
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:24,560
The white bridge over here

976
00:41:24,640 --> 00:41:27,040
brings all the colours together.

977
00:41:27,120 --> 00:41:29,080
- That's true.
- So pretty.

978
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:30,640
When you see it, you understand

979
00:41:30,720 --> 00:41:33,200
that those pine trees
are working very well.

980
00:41:33,280 --> 00:41:36,200
They have a deep green colour, which
looks great against other colours.

981
00:41:36,280 --> 00:41:38,640
That's why we get these colours.
I see.

982
00:41:38,720 --> 00:41:39,920
Narukokyo.

983
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:42,000
"Kyo" in Narukokyo
doesn't mean "bridge".

984
00:41:42,080 --> 00:41:44,600
It doesn't? I'm sorry.

985
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:47,160
I saw that this place
is called Narukokyo.

986
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:48,440
But it doesn't mean "bridge."

987
00:41:48,520 --> 00:41:49,480
I see.

988
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,360
Then what is that bridge?

989
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:54,640
Miyazon receives good news here.

990
00:41:54,720 --> 00:41:56,640
To the next autumn leaves spot,

991
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:57,680
we'll take a helicopter.

992
00:41:57,760 --> 00:41:59,480
Yes!

993
00:41:59,560 --> 00:42:01,320
Here it is!

994
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:02,920
Let's go!

995
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:04,240
- Awesome.
- Here.

996
00:42:04,320 --> 00:42:07,800
Now I'm back on the helicopter.

997
00:42:08,320 --> 00:42:10,720
The helicopter continues
to head north.

998
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:13,000
Then, something comes into view.

999
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:15,560
It's a massive lake!

1000
00:42:15,640 --> 00:42:17,800
It's huge!

1001
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:20,440
Here's the last autumn leaves spot.

1002
00:42:20,520 --> 00:42:22,480
Lake Towada, Aomori.

1003
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:24,200
Because of the complex terrain,

1004
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,240
there's a wide variety of trees,

1005
00:42:26,320 --> 00:42:29,400
where visitors enjoy
different types of autumn leaves.

1006
00:42:29,480 --> 00:42:32,680
Autumn leaves and a lake
look great together.

1007
00:42:32,760 --> 00:42:35,320
Let's go down then.

1008
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:36,840
Around that spot.

1009
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:38,400
Around there.

1010
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:39,760
Here we go.

1011
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,560
I came down.

1012
00:42:41,640 --> 00:42:43,520
Miyazon even travelled through time,

1013
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:45,040
and now it's sunrise time.

1014
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:46,840
The sun is rising slowly.

1015
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:48,640
I can see it!

1016
00:42:48,720 --> 00:42:50,880
It's a few centimetres away.

1017
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:53,400
Then the entire sun will appear.

1018
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:54,720
Then...

1019
00:42:55,240 --> 00:42:57,920
The sun has risen!

1020
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,480
It's beautiful!

1021
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:01,080
Ta-da!

1022
00:43:01,160 --> 00:43:03,280
- Good morning!
- Good morning.

1023
00:43:04,160 --> 00:43:06,360
When the sun rises,

1024
00:43:08,240 --> 00:43:12,440
autumn leaves are illuminated
by the sun, and glow orange.

1025
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:15,920
You don't get to have
a morning like this very often.

1026
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,240
You see?

1027
00:43:17,320 --> 00:43:19,600
You usually wake up to an alarm
to go to work.

1028
00:43:19,680 --> 00:43:23,000
You then set the snooze
for another 15 minutes.

1029
00:43:23,080 --> 00:43:25,040
Snooze, snooze.

1030
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:28,080
Many people have mornings like that,
but not today.

1031
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,920
Despite taking a lot of detours,

1032
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:34,600
Miyazon fully enjoyed autumn leaves
in different parts of Japan.

1033
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:36,200
How did you like it?

1034
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:37,120
Everyone has different opinions,

1035
00:43:37,200 --> 00:43:39,360
but I assume about
70 per cent of people

1036
00:43:39,440 --> 00:43:43,320
who watched the show
thought it looked wonderful.

1037
00:43:43,400 --> 00:43:46,920
Okay, now let's go back
to the studio!

1038
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,400
Here I go!

1039
00:43:49,680 --> 00:43:54,080
I do this to go up to an airplane
or come down from it.

1040
00:43:54,160 --> 00:43:58,640
That's all for Miyazon's
autumn leaves tour.

1041
00:43:58,720 --> 00:44:03,000
There were so many things
other than autumn leaves.

1042
00:44:03,080 --> 00:44:03,920
That's true.

1043
00:44:04,000 --> 00:44:05,640
It was quite messy.

1044
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,840
What I remember the most right now
is the amount of medicine.

1045
00:44:08,920 --> 00:44:12,600
- The cameraman's.
- Yes, Cameraman Yamamoto's.

1046
00:44:12,680 --> 00:44:16,280
But they only spent 30 seconds
to show each place.

1047
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:19,600
We'd be angry
if that happened to us.

1048
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:23,200
What I remember the most
is how delicious the ramen looked.

1049
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:24,160
It looked great!

